derivation.yuyuan_name: Middle English: probably from strip (from the notion of ‘narrowness’, i.e. slimness) + -ling

entry.def: People sometimes refer to a young man as a stripling when they want to indicate in a slightly humorous way that although he is no longer a boy, he is not yet really a man.

means.word_mean: 1. a juvenile between the onset of puberty and maturity
